%% Power tree — focused view, with currents and sequencing
%% Numbers are budgets, refine after datasheet review.

flowchart LR
    USBC[USB-C PD<br/>5V @ up to 3A]
    BENCH[Bench supply<br/>5V @ 5A]
    OR((5V_BOARD<br/>OR'd))
    USBC --> SS54_1[SS54] --> OR
    BENCH --> AO3401[AO3401A<br/>rev-pol P-FET] --> SS54_2[SS54] --> OR

    OR --> B33[Buck<br/>TPS54560x<br/>5V → 3V3 @ 1A]
    OR --> BARM[Buck<br/>TPS563201<br/>5V → 1V4 @ 600mA<br/>VDD_ARM_SOC]
    OR --> BDRAM[Buck<br/>TPS563201<br/>5V → 1V35 @ 400mA<br/>NVCC_DRAM DDR3L]
    OR --> LSNVS[LDO<br/>LDK220<br/>5V → 3V SNVS]

    B33 --> L18[LDO<br/>TLV75901<br/>3V3 → 1V8 @ 300mA]
    BDRAM --> LVTT[LDO<br/>TPS51200<br/>VTT = NVCC_DRAM/2 = 0.675V<br/>tracked, sink/source]

    COIN[CR2032<br/>RTC backup] -.-> LSNVS

    %% Consumers
    B33 --> CONS_3V3[/MPU NVCC_*, ETH PHY,<br/>I2S amp, CH340N, level translation/]
    BARM --> CONS_ARM[/MPU VDD_ARM_CAP<br/>VDD_SOC_IN/]
    BDRAM --> CONS_DRAM[/MPU NVCC_DRAM<br/>DDR3L Vdd/Vddq/]
    LVTT --> CONS_VTT[/DDR3L Vtt termination<br/>through Rtt/]
    L18 --> CONS_18[/SD/eMMC NVCC_SD,<br/>some MPU NVCC_*/]
    LSNVS --> CONS_SNVS[/MPU VDD_SNVS_CAP<br/>RTC + secure RAM/]

